What started out as a Planet of the Apes clone (after DC couldn't get the rights) quickly turned into yet another Jack Kirby showcase, as the King beautifully depicted this tale of a future apocalyptic world where animals rule mankind. Kirby's art is some of the most expressive of his career and his writing here is pretty good as well; he would end up writing the first 40 issues while the series itself lasted until issue 59. This torrent only presents the first 27 issues, as those have been re-released in digital form. These copies are thanks to Tyrant Lizard King-Empire - thanks to them for their work, and please seed and enjoy! :-)

As the tagline on the first issue states, &quot;Beasts that act like men! Men who act like beasts! See the world of...Kamandi, the last boy on earth!&quot;
